UID:10001046-1778009400-1778009400@townhallseattle.org
SUMMARY:Red May 2026: ICE-Age Policing
DESCRIPTION:Red May\, a month-long spree of red arts\, red theory\, and red politics based in Seattle\, Washington\, gathers each spring to discuss a world beyond capitalism. For this year’s event at Town Hall Seattle\, Red May brings together a panel to discuss policing in the age of ICE. \n“Counterinsurgency has come home. Since the end of the Vietnam War\, innovations in militarized policing have come one after another. No knock raids. AI surveillance. Clear and hold neighborhoods. Each new tactic or strategy has been rubber-stamped in Congress by both Democrats and Republicans under the guise of a never-ending War on Crime. Now\, the Trump administration has fashioned its own masked Gestapo; it has taken an existing organization designed for border control (ICE) and built it into a private army serving at the prerogative of the President\, most egregiously for assaults on Democrat-run cities like Portland\, and Chicago and the murder of protestors\, reclassified as ‘domestic terrorists.’ How did we get here? How do we get out of here?” \nJoin Red May and a panel of scholars to guide us through the labyrinth.
URL:https://townhallseattle.org/event/red-may-2026/
LOCATION:The Wyncote NW Forum\, 1119 8th Ave (Entrance off Seneca St.)\, Seattle\, 98101\, United States
CATEGORIES:Civics
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://townhallseattle.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/red-may-2026.jpg
END:VEVENT
